 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "Full Actors-pattern implementation (Governor + MarketEntry-LLM mock advisor + langgraph-clj StateGraph + append-only audit ledger + MemStore/DatomicStore), adapted from the cloud-itonami-iso3166-ago reference implementation and the cloud-itonami-iso3166-stp six-check pattern for thinner-dossier jurisdictions: src/marketentry/{facts,governor,registry,store,marketentryllm,operation,phase}.cljc + full test suite (governor contract, store contract MemStore=DatomicStore parity, registry pure-function, phase, facts) + docs/business-model.md + docs/operator-guide.md. The jurisdiction dossier (marketentry.facts) is intentionally THINNER than every sibling jurisdiction in this actor family, including the already-thin STP entry (2 required-evidence items vs STP's 3, AGO's 4): Sudan's public web presence for government/regulatory information is limited and current instability further limits verifiable current information, so this thinness is a deliberate, verifiable reflection of the research basis, not a shortcut. :owner-authority and :national-spec say so honestly rather than inventing a named regulator or an e-procurement portal that was not found. The governor is SIX checks (not AGO's seven -- no analog of AGO's nif-unverified check, since the dossier does not ground a distinct SDN tax-ID scheme separate from the Ministry of Justice commercial register / Ministry of Finance and Economic Planning company registration facts), and the demo engagement set is 4 engagements (a clean case, a registration-missing case, a fee-mismatch case, and a second clean case with a different fee shape). Grounded ONLY in a verified research dossier: the Procurement, Contracting & Disposal of Surplus Act (2010, implementing regulations 2011, World Bank PPP Knowledge Lab library); Ministry of Justice of Sudan (commercial register) and Ministry of Finance and Economic Planning (company registration) as the two registration authorities; Companies Act 1925 / Law on Registration 1971 / Law on Company Names 1931 as the corporate law basis; and the genuine in-person-only company-registration friction (no online registration in Sudan), documented honestly in docs/operator-guide.md rather than encoded as a governor check. This is Sudan (SDN), not South Sudan (SSD) -- two different countries with different ISO3166 codes and entirely separate legal/procurement systems; no South Sudan fact appears anywhere in this catalog."}
